text: Onepoto is a suburb of Porirua City in New Zealand. It is bounded to the north by Whitireia Park, a large park which is slowly being returned to native bush, and to the east by the Porirua Harbour. Onepoto had a population of 1,800 at the 2013 New Zealand census, a decrease of 45 people since the 2006 census. There were 885 males and 915 females. 70.3% were European/Pākehā, 30.9% were Māori, 16.3% were Pacific peoples and 4.5% were Asian. The New Zealand Ministry for Culture and Heritage gives a translation of "short beach" for Onepoto. == External links == *Onepoto Community Profile at Statistics NZ Category:Suburbs of Porirua
